{
  "stem": "490.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "The-- when you walked around with your uniform, you had your-- insignia that you're-- so they-- you were free to take-- to get some-- nothing special or nothing, but food or-- But all of a sudden, after a while, you started to see that life is more than just to survive and to-- especially when you are young, and you have-- life to seize in front of you.",
      "word_count": 68
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And you get sort of back to-- to-- your feelings come back to you and--",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I was 95 pounds.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I really, in the beginning-- as a matter of fact, I remember getting-- taking sick, ill once in a while.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember ending up in a hospital to be treated.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But it wasn't a-- it wasn't a serious thing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was sometimes over not to have the right food or not to do the right thing.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But we were-- we-- I recuperated very nicely, very easy.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, Goslar was-- Goslar was we lived there when we got to Goslar.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Goslar was-- oh.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Goslar--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, this was in '45. '45 we-- when we-- when I came out from this-- liberated in this Zwieberge.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Zwieberge was on the other side of the Elbe, which all of a sudden, we were told, there is the Russians are going to [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Russians are going to take over this part.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it's going to become East and West.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's going to be East and West.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So-- and we were told, if we want to stay with the Russians, we can stay.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But if we don't want to stay with the Russians, we should-- they'll provide us with transportation and to go across the Elbe to be where the-- with the British, where the British were.",
      "word_count": 34
    }
  ],
